{"metadata":{"name":"Sunan Ibn Majah","section":{"12":{"eng-name":"The Chapters on Business Transactions","ara-name":"كتاب التجارات"}},"section_detail":{"12":{"hadithnumber_first":2137,"hadithnumber_last":2307,"arabicnumber_first":2137,"arabicnumber_last":2307}}},"hadiths":[{"hadithnumber":2259,"arabicnumber":2259,"text":"It was narrated that Zuhri heard Malik bin Aws bin Hadathan say:\"I heard 'Umar say: \"The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ), said: 'Gold for silver is usury, unless it is exchanged on the spot.\"' (Sahih) Abu Bakr bin Abu-Shaibah said: \"I heard sufyan saying: 'Gold for silver.\" memorize (this)","grades":[{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Sahih Hadith"},{"name":"Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Shuaib Al Arnaut","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Zubair Ali Zai","grade":"Sahih - Agreed Upon"}],"reference":{"book":12,"hadith":123},"chapter":{"id":50,"ara-name":"باب صَرْفِ الذَّهَبِ بِالْوَرِقِ","eng-name":"Exchanging Gold For Silver","isFirstHadith":true}}]}